An Act to cap the amount by which a senior's property tax can increase.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 SECTION 1. Chapter 59 of the General Laws, as most recently amended by section 3 of
2 chapter 50 of the acts of 2023, is hereby further amended by inserting after section 5O the
3 following new section:-
4 Section 5P. With respect to each parcel of real property classified as Class One,
5 residential, in each city or town certified by the commissioner to be assessing all property at its
6 full and fair cash valuation, and at the option of the board of selectmen or mayor, with the
7 approval of the city council or local legislative body, may require that for a person who has
8 reached his sixty-fifth birthday prior to the fiscal year for which the property is assessed and
9 occupied by said person as his domicile, or of a person who owns the same jointly with his
10 spouse, that the assessed tax value of such real property may not increase more than a maximum
